@Pacheca12345 I'm personally in $NBIS, $CIFR, $IREN right now. Looking at $WULF next since short interest is high but $GOOGL happens to own 14% of it.

$CRWV obviously market leader so far, $WYFI, $SLNH, $GRRR, are more speculative ones.

Lot of people like $BITF, $CLSK, $HIVE on their pivot.

@dotsamaenjoyer At this point we're just arguing semantics. $WYFI is treated as $BTBT (the miner's) move into HPC.   

$WYFI alone is not a miner. $BTBT is a miner, and $WYFI is basically owned by $BTBT.  

So you're correct in saying $WYFI is not a miner, but $WYFI is basically a miner moving into HPC. Whitefiber was BTBT's internal HPC business, not a completely new organization. It's false they didn't repurpose any of their mining equipment or assets, but the facilities might not have been used for bitcoin mining before.

@dotsamaenjoyer Again I don't know why you're arguing semantics. 

I said none of them, including $NBIS, have cash flow + contracts visibility at scale and Coreweave is the only Neocloud actively doing $1B+ quarterly revenue. 

If $WYFI is doing $1B+ quarterly revenue now with visibility into margins after execution, let me know.

@dotsamaenjoyer That is literally semantics when I say $BTBT, a miner, that spun off their internal HPC segment $WYFI, is a miner moving into HPC. 

Individually $WYFI is not a miner, but when $BTBT a miner, is a majority owner of $WYFI and  they repurposed some of their assets from mining into HPC. $WYFI is a ( $BTBT) miner moving into HPC. 

You're right each miner repurposes different assets and have different risk profiles, but that literally is semantics.

@aasbadalados I said I’m bullish on just about almost every single Neocloud, including $WYFI!

The only point I made on other posts was that some neoclouds have higher asymmetrical returns than others like $NBIS.

On this post, I’m not making any single stock commentary, all were just examples
